  "text": "1) It is possible to impose a terminal, so-called capturability, constraint to ensure that within a particular preview horizon the system can be stopped, e.g., [CITATION_1] . Such constraint effectively prevents divergence, but may lead to infeasibility of the considered optimization problems. A detailed discussion of this topic can be found in [CITATION_2] .",
